result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:19 AM Defendant Jesse Patrick Wills in court.  Attorney Joseph Foster Rosenthal in court for Jesse Patrick Wills.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Attorney indicates agreement reached. Will plead to count 1 in 22CF106 file, count 2 dismissed. Will plead to Count 1 in 22CM129 file, remaining count to be dismissed. Remaining files dismissed but read in. 
Court recounts charges and possible penalties. Defendant pleads no contest in both files. Court informs defendant of rights given up by their plea. Attorney stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. Court finds Defendant understands all the rights they are waiving by their plea and freely and voluntarily waives those rights. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered. Count 2 in s22CF106, Counts 2 and 3 in 22cm129 are dismissed. in 22cm5, count 1 is dismissed but read in. in 21cm304, count 1 is dismissed but read in. 
Court orders in 22CF106, count 1, withheld for 2 years, conditions of probation are DOC programming, mandatory court costs, 6 days, 6 credit, no contact with domestic animals. In 22CM129, court orders 90 days jail, I&S for 1 years, conditions of probation, DOC programming, mandatory costs, 26 days, 26 credit, no contact with domestic animals.  Bail to be applied.
